# Walkthrough: Dual Database CQRS Implementation

## Overview

Project `cqrs-blog` telah berhasil di-refactor dari single database (PostgreSQL) menjadi **dual database CQRS**:

| Side | Database | Handlers |
|------|----------|----------|
| **Write (Command)** | PostgreSQL via GORM | [RoleCommandHandler](file:///I:/CQSR%20Hicollegues/cqrs-blog/internal/cqrs/handlers/role_command_handler.go#15-20), [UserCommandHandler](file:///I:/CQSR%20Hicollegues/cqrs-blog/internal/cqrs/handlers/user_command_handler.go#16-21), [PostCommandHandler](file:///I:/CQSR%20Hicollegues/cqrs-blog/internal/cqrs/handlers/post_command_handler.go#15-20) |
| **Read (Query)** | MongoDB | [RoleQueryHandler](file:///I:/CQSR%20Hicollegues/cqrs-blog/internal/cqrs/handlers/role_query_handler.go#15-18), [UserQueryHandler](file:///I:/CQSR%20Hicollegues/cqrs-blog/internal/cqrs/handlers/user_query_handler.go#15-18), [PostQueryHandler](file:///I:/CQSR%20Hicollegues/cqrs-blog/internal/cqrs/handlers/post_query_handler.go#15-18) |

## Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    Client["Client (API)"]

    subgraph Commands["Command Side (Write)"]
        CC["Command Controller"]
        CH["Command Handler"]
        PG[("PostgreSQL")]
    end

    subgraph Sync["Sync Layer"]
        SS["SyncService"]
    end

    subgraph Queries["Query Side (Read)"]
        QC["Query Controller"]
        QH["Query Handler"]
        MG[("MongoDB")]
    end

    Client -->|"POST/PUT/DELETE"| CC --> CH --> PG
    CH --> SS -->|"Upsert/Delete"| MG
    Client -->|"GET"| QC --> QH --> MG
```

